bib.title: Measurement of the differential cross sections andangle-integrated cross sections of the 6Li(n,t)4Hereaction from 1.0 eV to 3.0 MeV at the CSNS Back-nwhite neutron source

free_txt: The Back-n white neutron source at
China Spallation Neutron Source (CSNS)
Lile Liu(CNDC)
Fifteen rectangular silicon detectors (2 cm
x 2.5 cm, 500 um thick), 20 cm away from the center of
the 6LiF samples and covering angles from 19.2 deg to
160.8 deg, were used to measure the emitted charged
particles. In addition to the 15 silicon detectors, 3
delta E-E detectors and 1 GIC (gridded ionization
chamber) were also installed and tested.

6Li(n,t)4He cross sections
The Back-n white neutron source at
China Spallation Neutron Source (CSNS)
The neutrons were generated using the proton
beam (doublebunch, 25 Hz, 1.6 GeV, ~20 kW) to bombard
a tungsten target. The diameter of the neutron beam
was ~5.0 cm at Endstation, the neutron flight path
was 57.99 m, and the neutron flux was ~3.5E6 n/cm2s.
The beam duration for each turn was ~24 h, and
the total beam duration was ~196 h. The number of
protons hitting the tungsten target was used as the
normalization factor for background subtraction. The
uncertainty of the normalization factor was less than
0.03%, calibrated using the Si-Li detector array
installed on the neutron beam line.
The measured cross sections
were normalized according to standard cross section
from ENDF/B-VIII.0 in 0.1-0.4 MeV region.
Two enriched (90%) 6LiF samples were separately
evaporated on each side of a stainless steel sheet
0.10 mm thick. Their thickness was 776 and 787
ug/cm2. Their diameter and non-uniformity were 50 mm
and 5%, respectively.

The angle-integrated cross sections were
obtained from Table A3 of Appendix A of Chinese Phys.
C 44,1(2020)014003. The detailed uncertainties were
obtained from Huaiyong Bai.
Angular distribution
The differential cross sections were obtained
from Table A1-A3 of Appendix A of Chinese Phys. C
44,1(2020)014003. The detailed uncertainties were
obtained from Huaiyong Bai.
